Loan Programs
Design like Movement’s loan overview: grid of cards by group, each linking to a dedicated SEO page for that program.
​

Top intro

Brief explanation of:

Purchase vs Refinance vs Self-employed / No-doc.

Guidance CTA: “Not sure what fits? Schedule a 10‑minute strategy call.”

Group 1: Mua nhà (Purchase)

Cards:

Conventional

Who it’s for, minimum down, key benefits.

Link: /loan-programs/conventional-mortgage

FHA

Lower down, flexible credit, ideal for many first-time buyers.
​

Link: /loan-programs/fha-loan

VA (if available)

0% down for eligible veterans, no monthly mortgage insurance.
​

Link: /loan-programs/va-loan

First-time homebuyer guidance

Education, down payment assistance, hand-holding through process.

Link: /loan-programs/first-time-homebuyer-pa

Group 2: Refinance

Rate & Term Refi

Lower payment, shorter term, remove PMI.

Link: /loan-programs/rate-term-refinance

Cash-out Refi

Tap equity for renovations, debt consolidation, investing.

Link: /loan-programs/cash-out-refinance

Group 3: Không chứng minh thu nhập / Self-employed

Bank statement loans

Qualify using 12–24 months business/personal bank statements.

Link: /loan-programs/bank-statement-mortgage

P&L / VOE only

Profit & Loss and/or Verification of Employment driven structures.

Link: /loan-programs/p-and-l-voe-mortgage

DSCR loans

For investors; qualify based on property’s rental income vs payment (DSCR).

Link: /loan-programs/dscr-investor-loan

Per‑program SEO subpage layout (all similar)

